name: Stephanie
key_opinion: Stephanie, a Professor of pediatrics at the University of California San Diego, is focused on the molecular characterization of cystinosis and metabolic circulatory disease and gene therapy. She discussed the complex nature of cystinosis, an autosomal recessive metabolic disease, and her work in advancing gene therapy approaches for systemic genetic disorders. Her work significantly improves the quality of life for patients with gene therapy, focusing on using stem cells to replace missing proteins in genetic diseases.
